metadata.name: Pandora II, 8,750 ft.
metadata.description:
Pandora II, 8,750 ft. was created as an 20x24in ambrotype original, taken with a restored Levy Process Camera from the 1920's.  

This was taken of Idorado Mine in Pandora, which is one of Tellurides more well-known historic mines from the 19th century.

This work was created while during artist in residences at Steeprock Artisans Guild and Telluride Mountain Film Festival.  

At the time of minting this NFT, the original is still at my studio in Santa Barbara, CA.  


1 of 1 NFT, 3000px x 2568px
